'''Level 6.2''' is a sub-level between [[Level 6]] and [[Level 7]] within The Backrooms. It is widely regarded as one of, if not the most dangerous, levels of the Main Nine, serving as a significant obstruction when it comes to further exploration.
==<span style="position: relative; display: inline-block; margin-right: 2.5px; top: -2px;">[[File:Untitled205 20240925204431.png|30px|link=]]</span> Description==
{{Blurimage|file=Aspenforest1.png|caption=An image of '''Level 6.2'''. Photographer unknown.}}
'''Level 6.2''' is a sprawling aspen forest set in perpetual dusk, with the only prevalent light sources being from the abundant eyelike formations that occur naturally on the level's trees. Covering the forest floor is a diverse number of brush crops — along with other natural vegetation, the majority of which are dead and wilting due to extended dehydration. The forest floor within '''Level 6.2''' is unstable and henceforth prone to collapse, with many pitfalls strewn about the terrain which often lead to [[The Void]]. The level also contains a prevalent temporal anomaly — as time moves at an estimated 6.2 times slower than it would in most levels. 

Throughout the massive forests, one may come across large clearings, usually fields of valleys. The ground of these clearings is mostly covered in yellow-brown grass, with the grass emitting a rancid stench. In some of these large clearings, there may be massive stone obelisks. These stone obelisks contain texts written in indecipherable glyphs and lexicons. What purpose said obelisks serve is yet to be revealed, though some theorize they are exits to other levels, or otherwise thresholds of some sort. In rare cases, the eyelike formations found on the aspen trees can also be observed manifesting on the stone obelisks.

Auditory hallucinations are frequently experienced in '''Level 6.2''', ranging from the distant chirping of birds to indecipherable voices echoing throughout the forest. It is widely believed that the level can influence one's perception of reality, resulting in symptoms such as paranoia and derealization. As a result of such factors, as well as the level's sheer darkness, it is widely considered that '''Level 6.2''' is the most dangerous in the Main Nine, with most wanderers who enter this level either submitting to [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]] or perishing due to [[Phenomenon 25|related factors]].

The auditory hallucinations and paranoia experienced in '''Level 6.2''' are all results of being exposed to its oppressive darkness, as the prevalent sanity deprivation is typically a result of the lack of sleep from the loss of time or isolation, and a lack of mental stimulation. After extended periods within '''Level 6.2''', further exploration becomes significantly more difficult — due to fatigue and constant, involuntary bursts of rest, known as microsleep, with the profound darkness having a detrimental psychological effect on the human body.
==<span style="position: relative; display: inline-block; margin-right: 2.5px; top: -2px;">[[File:Untitled205 20240925204431.png|30px|link=]]</span> Addendum==
<div style="text-align: center; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0); border: double 4.5px white; padding: 10px;>
<center><big><big>'''''The Eyes'''''</big></big><br>
"Give In"</center>
Step. Step. Step.

The forest is eerie. The small ponds in the ground soak my feet, the water cold. The trees around me emit a disturbing aura. The eyes carved into them stare at me, as if they were angry. It really is a lonely walk. I could hear an ambient noise, which was strange to me because I had gone deaf long ago. And yet I could not get rid of the feeling that something or someone is following me. The eyes on those trees are trying to control me. Trying to possess me, but I will not give in. Not now, not ever. 

Suddenly, I hear a voice call out for me in the distance.

"Hello? Randall? I'm scared..."

The voice sounded familiar. How did it know my name?

"It's me, Wendy. Please help, I'm so cold..."

Wendy? My sister? There is no possible way she could be here. She had gone missing back [[Level 0|in that place]]. But could it be?

"Please help. The eyes trapped me in one of these trees. It's so dark in here..."

Without any hesitation, I look up. I scan each tree, every nook and cranny for her. But then, at that moment, the voice shifts.

I turn around.

"'''Goodbye, Randall. It is already too late.'''"

The voice deepened, soon becoming incomprehensible. That is when I knew something was wrong. It had tricked me. But before I could turn away, it had already locked me into its eternal gaze.

"Come with me, Randall."
</div>
==<span style="position: relative; display: inline-block; margin-right: 2.5px; top: -2px;">[[File:Untitled205 20240925204431.png|30px|link=]]</span> Entity Presence==
{{Fullscreen|num=1|show=> Open Attached File?|hide=> Close Attached File?|content= 
{{Background|file=Dark6.png}}
<div style="text-align: center;">
='''The Eyes'''=
[[File:ASPEN.png|center]]

The Eyes are a level-exclusive entity that can only be found within '''Level 6.2''', and it is the only entity that resides in it. At first glance, the eyelike formations on the level's trees seem like nothing but a creepy decoration. However, there is more to them than meets the eye.

The Eyes are, in theory, one omnipotent, omnipresent being controlling the level, including its nature and surroundings; hence, the level is essentially one giant sentient superorganism. The entity can be seen everywhere one goes and everywhere one stops. It makes up almost the entire level, with it appearing on the aspen trees, the stone obelisks, as well as other parts of the level.

The Eyes' main attacking method is believed to be to intentionally inconvenience the wanderer through mental attacks, as upon being looked at, it can cause detrimental psychological effects on wanderers. At first, it can cause visual and auditory hallucinations, stress, paranoia, headaches, etc. However, the longer it stares at someone, the worse the psychological effects get. When stared at for long periods, the number and intensity of these effects grow, causing physical injuries, unstable aggression, and eventually leading to either [[Phenomenon 35|insanity]] or death. And as The Eyes can be found everywhere, it is a serious threat that brings grave danger to all wanderers who enter the level.

Although looking downwards is a solid solution, it is ultimately useless, as The Eyes seem to be masters at manipulation. When not looked at, The Eyes intentionally use ambient noise to grab and distract wanderers' attention, annoying them until they are forced to look at it. If this method fails, the ambient noise will slowly grow louder until it reaches a deafening level, eventually killing the wanderer from the sheer volume. In extremely rare cases, if a wanderer is resilient enough to withstand this loud noise, The Eyes will mimic a person's voice and call the wanderer forward to put the final nail in the coffin.

If you feel like you are incapable of controlling yourself, give in. It is only a matter of time before its glare catches up to you.
</div>
